h3cPosa.name: h3cPosa

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

h3cPosa.contactinfo: PLAT Team Hangzhou H3C Technologies Co.,Ltd. Shang-Di Information Industry Base, Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cPosa.description: This MIB is to provide the definition of the POSA (Point Of Sale Access) system.

H3cAppServiceType.name: H3cAppServiceType
H3cAppServiceType.description: The service type of a POS application. It means the way in which the router connects with the application server. At present, it supports two service types, tcp(1) and flow(2). If the router connects with the server through SEARIAL/ASYNC interface, the service type is flow(1). If through TCP/IP, the service type is tcp(1).

H3cAppMode.name: H3cAppMode
H3cAppMode.description: The work mode of a POS application. It has two value normal(1) and temporary(2). This attribute is valid only when the service type is tcp(1). If it works in temporary(2) mode, the TCP connection between router and application server is established when a POS trade begins and disconnected when a POS trade finishes. In normal(1) mode, the TCP connection is established when POS function is enabled and exists all along.

H3cPeerState.name: H3cPeerState
H3cPeerState.description: The current running state of the peer (application server or POS terminal) of the router. notset(1) The peer is not configured correctly. down(2) The interface connecting with the peer is down. up(3) The interface connecting with the peer is up. kept(4) The connection between router and the peer is not established. linking(5) The connection between router and the peer is establishing. linked(6) The connection between router and the peer is established. multilink(7) There are multiple connections between router and the peer. blocked(8) The connection between router and the peer is unreachable. The status of down(2) and up(3) appear only when the router and the peer are connected with interface. The status about TCP connections appear when the router and the peer are connected with TCP/IP.

H3cTerminalAccessType.name: H3cTerminalAccessType
H3cTerminalAccessType.description: The access type of a POS terminal. Now it supports 3 types. fcm(1) The POS terminal connects with router through FCM interface. flow(2) The POS terminal connects with router through SERIAL, ASYNC, AM (Analog Modem) or AUX interface. tcp(3) The POS terminal connects with router through TCP/IP protocol. The default access type is fcm(2).

H3cTpduChangeStrategy.name: H3cTpduChangeStrategy
H3cTpduChangeStrategy.description: The strategy to modify the address of the packet from terminals before delivering it to application server. Now it supports 2 types. ChangeTpduSrc(1) Replace the source address of the packet with POSID. ChangeTpduDest(2) Replace the destination address of the packet with POSID.

h3cPosaServerEnable.name: h3cPosaServerEnable
h3cPosaServerEnable.description: This attribute controls the starting or stoppage of POS access function. The defalut value is disabled(1).

h3cPosaFcmAnswerTimeout.name: h3cPosaFcmAnswerTimeout
h3cPosaFcmAnswerTimeout.description: The maximum answer time of a POS connection through a FCM (Fast Connection Modem) interface. The answer time is the interval from the POS terminal sending request to the Router giving its reply, in units of milliseconds.

h3cPosaFcmTradeTimeout.name: h3cPosaFcmTradeTimeout
h3cPosaFcmTradeTimeout.description: The maximum time of a POS trade through a FCM interface, in units of milliseconds.

h3cPosaFcmIdleTimeout.name: h3cPosaFcmIdleTimeout
h3cPosaFcmIdleTimeout.description: The maximum idle time of a POS connection through the FCM interface, in units of seconds.

h3cPosaSrvStateChangeTrapEnable.name: h3cPosaSrvStateChangeTrapEnable
h3cPosaSrvStateChangeTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the h3cPosaServerStatusChange trap will be sent or not.

h3cPosaAppStateChangeTrapEnable.name: h3cPosaAppStateChangeTrapEnable
h3cPosaAppStateChangeTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the h3cPosaAppStateChange trap will be sent or not.

h3cPosaTerminalHangUpTrapEnable.name: h3cPosaTerminalHangUpTrapEnable
h3cPosaTerminalHangUpTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the h3cPosaTerminalHangUp trap will be sent or not.

h3cPosaFcmLnkNegoFailTrapEnable.name: h3cPosaFcmLnkNegoFailTrapEnable
h3cPosaFcmLnkNegoFailTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the h3cPosaFcmLinkNegoFailed trap will be sent or not.

h3cPosaFcmPhyNegoFailTrapEnable.name: h3cPosaFcmPhyNegoFailTrapEnable
h3cPosaFcmPhyNegoFailTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the h3cPosaFcmPhyNegoFailed trap will be sent or not.

h3cPosaAppTable.name: h3cPosaAppTable
h3cPosaAppTable.description: This table shows the configuration information and running status of POS application.

h3cPosaAppEntry.name: h3cPosaAppEntry
h3cPosaAppEntry.description: This table shows the configuration information and running status of POS application.

h3cPosaAppID.name: h3cPosaAppID
h3cPosaAppID.description: The identification of a POS application. It ranges from 1 to 31.

h3cPosaAppServiceType.name: h3cPosaAppServiceType
h3cPosaAppServiceType.description: The service type of a POS application. It means the way in which the router connects with the application server.

h3cPosaAppIfIndex.name: h3cPosaAppIfIndex
h3cPosaAppIfIndex.description: This attribute is the ifindex through which the router connecting with the application server, if the service type of POS application is flow(2). It is invalid if the service type is tcp(1). At preasent, it supports 5 types of interface: FCM, SERIAL, ASYNC, AM (Analog Modem) and AUX.

h3cPosaAppMode.name: h3cPosaAppMode
h3cPosaAppMode.description: The work mode of a POS application.

h3cPosaAppHostIPType.name: h3cPosaAppHostIPType
h3cPosaAppHostIPType.description: The IP address type of the application server. And now it must be IPV4. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

h3cPosaAppHostIP.name: h3cPosaAppHostIP
h3cPosaAppHostIP.description: The IP address of the application server. And now it only supports IPV4. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

h3cPosaAppHostPort.name: h3cPosaAppHostPort
h3cPosaAppHostPort.description: The listening port of the application server. If the information of the application server is not specified, this object will return the value 0. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

h3cPosaAppRouterIPType.name: h3cPosaAppRouterIPType
h3cPosaAppRouterIPType.description: The source IP address type of the access router. Now it must be ipv4. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

h3cPosaAppRouterIP.name: h3cPosaAppRouterIP
h3cPosaAppRouterIP.description: The source IP address of access router used in connecting with application server. Now it only supports ipv4. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

h3cPosaAppKeepAliveInterval.name: h3cPosaAppKeepAliveInterval
h3cPosaAppKeepAliveInterval.description: The TCP keep alive interval of the connection between the router and the application server. In unit of seconds. The default value is 2 seconds. It is valid only when the service type is tcp(1).

h3cPosaAppKeepAliveCount.name: h3cPosaAppKeepAliveCount
h3cPosaAppKeepAliveCount.description: The maximum number of sending TCP keep alive packets. It is valid only when the service type is tcp(1).

h3cPosaAppConnectTimeout.name: h3cPosaAppConnectTimeout
h3cPosaAppConnectTimeout.description: The maximum interval that the router waits for the reply from application server after sending the request for establishing a TCP connection. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

h3cPosaAppState.name: h3cPosaAppState
h3cPosaAppState.description: The current running state of application server.

h3cPosaAppName.name: h3cPosaAppName
h3cPosaAppName.description: The description of a POS application.

h3cPosaCallerIDTransEnable.name: h3cPosaCallerIDTransEnable
h3cPosaCallerIDTransEnable.description: Enable or disable the caller-id transmission function.

h3cPosaTpduChangeStrategy.name: h3cPosaTpduChangeStrategy
h3cPosaTpduChangeStrategy.description: Set the strategy to modify the address of the packet from terminals before delivering it to application server.

h3cPosaBackupAppID.name: h3cPosaBackupAppID
h3cPosaBackupAppID.description: Specify the backup application ID, 0 indicates not using backup application. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

h3cPosaQuietTimeOut.name: h3cPosaQuietTimeOut
h3cPosaQuietTimeOut.description: Specify the wait time for re-activating application server. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

h3cPosaAppHello.name: h3cPosaAppHello
h3cPosaAppHello.description: Specify the switch of hello packet for the application server.

h3cPosaAppHelloInterval.name: h3cPosaAppHelloInterval
h3cPosaAppHelloInterval.description: Specify the interval time in minute(s) of hello packet.

h3cPosaAppRouterPort.name: h3cPosaAppRouterPort
h3cPosaAppRouterPort.description: The source port of access router used in connecting with application server. 0 indicates not to specify the source port. It is valid only if the service type is tcp(1) and mode is normal(1).

h3cPosaTerminalTable.name: h3cPosaTerminalTable
h3cPosaTerminalTable.description: This table shows the configuration information and running status of POS terminal.

h3cPosaTerminalEntry.name: h3cPosaTerminalEntry
h3cPosaTerminalEntry.description: This table shows the configuration information and running status of POS terminal.

h3cPosaTerminalID.name: h3cPosaTerminalID
h3cPosaTerminalID.description: The identification of a POS terminal.

h3cPosaTerminalAccessType.name: h3cPosaTerminalAccessType
h3cPosaTerminalAccessType.description: The access type of a POS terminal.

h3cPosaTerminalIfIndex.name: h3cPosaTerminalIfIndex
h3cPosaTerminalIfIndex.description: The ifindex of the interface through which connects the POS terminal and the router. It is invalid if the access type is TCP.

h3cPosaTerminalTransAppID.name: h3cPosaTerminalTransAppID
h3cPosaTerminalTransAppID.description: The identification of the application server to which all the packets from this POS terminal will be sent. If this object is set to 0, the destination application server to which a packet from this POS terminal will be sent is determined by its TPDU (Transport Protocol Data Unit) destination address. It is invalid if the access type is TCP.

h3cPosaTerminalListenPort.name: h3cPosaTerminalListenPort
h3cPosaTerminalListenPort.description: The listening port accepting the connection from POS terminals. It is valid only when the access type is TCP.

h3cPosaTerminalState.name: h3cPosaTerminalState
h3cPosaTerminalState.description: The current running status of a POS terminal.

h3cPosaTerminalName.name: h3cPosaTerminalName
h3cPosaTerminalName.description: The description of a POS terminal.

h3cPosaTerminalCfgIfIndex.name: h3cPosaTerminalCfgIfIndex
h3cPosaTerminalCfgIfIndex.description: The ifindex of the interface on which the terminal configuration is. If it is a physical interface, its value is equal to that of h3cPosaTerminalIfIndex.

h3cPosaMapTable.name: h3cPosaMapTable
h3cPosaMapTable.description: This table describe the application-mapping information.

h3cPosaMapEntry.name: h3cPosaMapEntry
h3cPosaMapEntry.description: This table describe the application-mapping information.

h3cPosaMapDestCode.name: h3cPosaMapDestCode
h3cPosaMapDestCode.description: The destination code of the mapping item. Generally, the destination code is a 4-character-string. If the destination address in POS packet matches the code, the packet will be deliveried to the corresponding application server. If any code can not be matched, the packet will be deliveried to the default server. A special destination code, 'default', is for default mapping item.

h3cPosaMapAppID.name: h3cPosaMapAppID
h3cPosaMapAppID.description: The identifier of POS application. It is the index of h3cPosaAppTable.

h3cPosaMapSrcCode.name: h3cPosaMapSrcCode
h3cPosaMapSrcCode.description: The source code of the mapping item. Generally, the source code is a 4-character-string. If the source address in POS packet matches the code, the packet will be deliveried to the corresponding application server. If any code can not be matched, the packet will be deliveried to the default server. A special source code, 'default', is for default mapping item.

h3cPosaFcmStatTransCntsClear.description: Clear the number of successful transactions and all transactions.

h3cPosaTcpTermStatIPMask.description: The mask associated with the IP address or the subnet. And now it only supports ipv4.

h3cPosaFcmLinkNegoFailed.description: This trap is generated whenever the link layer negotiation is failed between the POS terminal and router through a FCM (Fast Connection Modem) interface.

h3cPosaFcmPhyNegoFailed.description: This trap is generated whenever the physical layer negotiation is failed between the POS terminal and router through a FCM (Fast Connection Modem) interface.
